{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"acid-pepperish-mare","description":"# Retarget provider shims to AGENTS.md + repo-wide reference sweep + optional per-tool pointers\n\n## Why\n\nOnce `AGENTS.md` is canonical, the existing shims and scattered `CLAUDE.md` references must be\nreconciled so nothing points at stale guidance, and we should decide which (if any) low-cost\nper-tool pointer files are worth adding. `.codex/config.toml` currently falls back to `CLAUDE.md`\nwith a comment saying it's temporary \"until the guidance is migrated\" — this story completes that\nmigration. `.agents/rules/rebar.md` is a hand-maintained neutral distillation that must not drift\nfrom the new `AGENTS.md`.\n\n## What\n\n(1) Update `.codex/config.toml` so Codex reads `AGENTS.md` natively (remove/adjust the CLAUDE.md\nfallback and the \"temporary shim\" comment). (2) Reconcile `.agents/rules/rebar.md` with the new\n`AGENTS.md` (reduce to a pointer or align content; eliminate drift). (3) Sweep the repo for\n`CLAUDE.md` references (`CONTRIBUTING.md`, `docs/`, `README.md`, tests, `.github/workflows/`) and\nupdate each to the new structure — or confirm it intentionally targets the thin file. (4) Decide\nand record whether to add optional per-tool pointers: `.github/copilot-instructions.md` (for\nCopilot IN-EDITOR) and a Gemini `context.fileName` note; any added must be pointers to `AGENTS.md`,\nnot duplicated content. Keep the module-size gate and all CI green.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: `.codex/config.toml`, `.agents/rules/rebar.md`, reference updates across docs/CONTRIBUTING/\nREADME/tests/CI, and optional pointer files. Out: the root-file and template changes (their own\nstories). Depends on: the AGENTS.md story and the CLAUDE.local.md story (sweep runs after the\ncanonical files exist).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `.codex/config.toml` reads `AGENTS.md` natively; the \"temporary/until migrated\" wording is\n  gone.\n  - Proving: `rg -c 'CLAUDE.md|temporary' .codex/config.toml` reflects the completed migration.\n- [ ] `.agents/rules/rebar.md` is consistent with `AGENTS.md` (pointer or aligned), no drift.\n- [ ] Every remaining `CLAUDE.md` reference in the repo is intentional or updated.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'CLAUDE\\.md' --glob '!CLAUDE.md'` reviewed line-by-line in the change.\n- [ ] Decision on optional Copilot/Cursor/Gemini per-tool files is recorded; any added are\n  pointers, not duplicated content.\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` pass and the module-size CI gate is green.","id":"5b01-add0-e970-44bd","parent_id":"81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Retarget provider shims to AGENTS.md + repo-wide reference sweep + optional per-tool pointers"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784230965710933001,"uuid":"edaa02fb-78f8-45cb-b6d6-c03e0a8ce606"}